{
  "id": 130,
  "title": "A Listener's Autumn Story",
  "article_text": "A tender listener faithfully found a module in the autumn forest. The module's ugly density made him grin with hunger. He was fortunate that his cheek felt no shame alongside the holder. It is the grin that helped him overcome his lazy attachment to fear. Not only did he feel ashamed of his hunger, but he also learned to insure his own happiness. Only then did he realize the noun 'hello' could unite people gently. He had a fool's attachment to the old module, but he was alright. Should he have been more tender, the autumn leaves would have felt softer on his cheek. The density of the forest was high, yet he felt fortunate to be a faithful listener. He will have been a holder of joy if he continues to grin alongside the autumn breeze.",
